        // data exchange (gpu/SPEC.md §5). Lowers to
        //   `shfl.sync.idx.b32 %r<dst>, %r<src>, %r<lane>, 0x1f, 0xffffffff;`
        // — the `idx` mode selects the source lane by its index; `0x1f`
        // c-operand encodes lane-mask=31 (full warp) + clamp-mode=idx;
        // `0xffffffff` is the membermask covering all 32 warp lanes
        // (matches CUDA's `__shfl_sync` __FULL_MASK). 32-bit baseline
        // (`.b32`) per the §12 P4+ first slice — FP64 / 64-bit shuffle
        // composes from two 32-bit halves in a later sub-phase. The dst
        // Local is U32 (matching `_nvptx_classify_local_for_stmt` rule
        // below); the value + lane operands render via hand-typed
        // `_nvptx_reg_u32(<arg local_id>)` references — the PTX shfl.sync
        // 32-bit form requires `.b32`-class registers for both inputs.
        //   ref: NVIDIA PTX ISA §9.7.13.4 shfl.sync.
        if s.op == "gpu_warp_shuffle" {
            if len(s.args) >= 2 {
                // N71-B (N70/N91 GAP-C) — FP64 source decompose/recompose.
                // `shfl.sync.idx.b32` moves only 32 bits; an f64 value
